reviews.review_text: Sweet sweet show Set list wise there was nothing about this show that particularly stands out .... but the Loose Lucy bust out was a shock and it was amazing being there to realize that that was what was happening. And it was stellar. I would apply that to most of the rest of this show; especially the Crazy Fingers and Black Peter. There being three songs pre-drums in the second set, there was a lot of time for jamming and exploring weird territory. They did not use this time idly by any means. Lots of truly inspired weirdness with Phil being on on on and the rest of the band being just as strong. The recording is very crisp and fat. It's a true pity that the taper had to adjust the levels during the Loose Lucy. Of all the L.L.s that I've heard, I never heard one with this much energy. Try to find it on another recording where it is not so compromised by taping blotches. Wish I were there again.
